<div style="max-width:720px">

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:var(--fs-sm);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin:0 0 20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink-line)">About Quorum1</h2>

  <div class="faq-list">

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        What is a meta-consultancy?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">A meta-consultancy is a globally distributed coalition of boutique agencies and independent professionals that markets and delivers collectively — acting as one trusted front door while preserving each member's independence. Quorum1 is the first to apply this model explicitly to systems change work.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        What is systems change work?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Systems change work addresses root causes rather than symptoms — redesigning the governance structures, financial models, legal frameworks, and coordination mechanisms that shape how organizations and communities operate. It includes governance design, regenerative finance, commons law, network stewardship, and organizational innovation.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        Is Quorum1 a company?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Quorum1 is an ecomimetic collective — an organization that practices the same regenerative, commons-based principles it helps clients adopt. There is no single parent company. The brand is collectively stewarded by member organizations through a transparent governance stack. Revenue flows to practitioners and nodes, not shareholders.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:var(--fs-sm);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin:48px 0 20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink-line)">For clients</h2>

  <div class="faq-list">

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        How do I hire the Quorum1 network?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Start at <a href="/hire/">the hire page</a>, browse service offerings, or reach out directly. You brief us once — we route your project to the best-aligned practitioners and assemble the right team. No RFP maze, no account managers, no lock-in.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        What kinds of projects does Quorum1 take on?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Governance redesigns, treasury architecture, commons law advisory, org design, regenerative finance modeling, network stewardship, sense-making infrastructure, and more. If your project touches how an organization governs itself, finances itself, or coordinates — we likely have the right practitioners.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:700;font-size:var(--fs-sm);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-mute);margin:48px 0 20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--ink-line)">For members</h2>

  <div class="faq-list">

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        What does it cost to join?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Individual practitioners join free. Member organizations pay a small onboarding contribution ($400–$600 USD) to cover administrative costs and demonstrate commitment to the collective. There are no ongoing dues.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        How do nodes work?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Nodes are self-governing member collectives organized around a practice area (governance design, regenerative finance, etc.) or geography (North America, EU, etc.). 10% of every Quorum1 project routes to the relevant practice node, and 10% to the relevant region node. Nodes use this revenue to fund their own sales, marketing, research, and member support. See <a href="/how-it-works/">how it works</a> for the full model.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
        Can I be a member and still work for other clients independently?
        <svg class="faq-chevron" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes — always. Quorum1 membership adds to your practice; it doesn't constrain it. Members retain complete independence and can work with any client, through any channel. The Quorum1 network is additive, not exclusive.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

